  "body": "Geth version: 1.8.12+build14270+bionic\r\nOS & Version: Ubuntu 18.04 in a VM on a Windows 10 box\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nSyncing\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nLooping through peers on block 150000 with BAD BLOCK Error: invalid mix digest:\r\n\r\nERROR[07-07|17:36:18.798] \r\n########## BAD BLOCK #########\r\nChain config: {ChainID: 1 Homestead: 1150000 DAO: 1920000 DAOSupport: true EIP150: 2463000 EIP155: 2675000 EIP158: 2675000 Byzantium: 4370000 Constantinople: <nil> Engine: ethash}\r\nNumber: 150000\r\nHash: 0x79a3fc34bae954e87cffbc0dfe682ca69af2ecdc4a53acbe680ab33445136483\r\nError: invalid mix digest\r\n##############################\r\n \r\nWARN [07-07|17:36:18.799] Synchronisation failed, dropping peer    peer=5d59b8b861d1b971 err=\"retrieved hash chain is invalid\"\r\nWARN [07-07|17:38:08.512] Synchronisation failed, retrying         err=\"block download canceled (requested)\"\r\nERROR[07-07|17:39:55.796] \r\n########## BAD BLOCK #########\r\nChain config: {ChainID: 1 Homestead: 1150000 DAO: 1920000 DAOSupport: true EIP150: 2463000 EIP155: 2675000 EIP158: 2675000 Byzantium: 4370000 Constantinople: <nil> Engine: ethash}\r\nNumber: 150000\r\nHash: 0x79a3fc34bae954e87cffbc0dfe682ca69af2ecdc4a53acbe680ab33445136483\r\nError: invalid mix digest\r\n##############################\r\netc in an apparently infinite loop through different peers\r\n\r\nNote that I experienced a similar loop on block 5914885 with version 1.8.11:\r\nERROR[07-07|07:18:44]\r\n########## BAD BLOCK #########\r\nChain config: {ChainID: 1 Homestead: 1150000 DAO: 1920000 DAOSupport: true EIP150: 2463000 EIP155: 2675000 EIP158: 2675000 Byzantium: 4370000 Constantinople: <nil> Engine: ethash}\r\nNumber: 5914885\r\nHash: 0x45caa31422b187cf12054279f0792b65596900dfa844a0addec510cfada0e563\r\nError: nonce too high\r\n##############################\r\n\r\nbefore trying from the start again with 1.8.12 only to get stuck on block 150000 as above!\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\ngeth removedb\r\ngeth --cache=4096 --syncmode \"full\"\r\n\r\n",
